This issue has been published,239 with the curious word at the end of the reverse margin read as . The letters before the final alif are clearly ḥā (jīm, etc.), and either qāf (or fā) or mīm;
                     perhaps the word is حقًا,240 "truly, verily," a pious expression used by the die-engraver to fill up the
                     excess space in the margin.

